ation make for ideological radicalism? And what impact do these first steps have on Buñuel's subsequent work and his later ideological trajectory? María Soledad Fernández Utrera is Associate Professor of Spanish at The University of British Columbia.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn Spanish, Castilian.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 4aFilm & Theatre. 4aHispanic Studies. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / Spanish & Portuguese.2bisacsh  aOrder of Toledo.  aSpain.  aSpanish.  aart history.  afilm and media studies.  ahistory of Spain.  aknighthood.  atwentieth century Spanish art.  atwentieth century Spanish literature.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311143131440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781782045816423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781782045816/original  a978-3-11-143131-4  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles